{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"rink-ledge-valor","description":"## Summary\nThe mirror-guard workflow fails on every evaluation: permissions declares 'administration: read', which is NOT a valid GITHUB_TOKEN workflow-permission scope, so the workflow fails schema validation and no jobs run (0-job 'startup failure'). Even if valid, its ruleset-drift check needs a GitHub token with administration:read (a fine-grained PAT), which org policy won't grant the default token.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Push to main (or trigger mirror-guard).\n2. Observe: run created with 0 jobs, conclusion=failure, 'log not found'.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: mirror-guard runs and verifies Gerrit->GitHub replication using the default token.\n- Actual: workflow fails validation (invalid permission key) and never runs.\n\n## Fix\nScope the Actions workflow to the REPLICATION check only (rebar.mirror_guard --replication), which needs no admin token (fetch_github_main_sha treats the token as optional; Gerrit read is anonymous). Drop the ruleset-drift check from this workflow and remove the invalid administration:read permission, so it runs on the default GITHUB_TOKEN (contents: read) with no PAT.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] mirror-guard.yml permissions contains no invalid keys (drops administration:read; keeps contents: read).\n- [ ] The workflow runs 'rebar.mirror_guard --replication' (no ruleset check), needing no fine-grained PAT.\n- [ ] mirror-guard is green on main (replication in sync) without any new secret.","id":"3b37-abf4-61f4-4d2b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"mirror-guard CI red: invalid administration:read permission + PAT-only ruleset check"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783289633217493001,"uuid":"7f4a00ca-8811-4683-8ceb-92663d28477c"}